Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.90,0:01:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Shinobu's unit, deployed to the front line, found itself marooned by the headquarters
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.00,0:01:24.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and forced to face off a whole battalion of cossacks with a single platoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.54,0:01:28.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Having vowed to bring everyone home alive, Shinobu returned to look for injured Onijima,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.99,0:01:32.52,Default,,0,0,0,,recklessly jumping into the smokes of the battlefield all alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.95,0:01:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Although repeatedly called on, he never returned.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.93,0:01:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the tragic fate
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.55,0:01:43.42,Default,,0,0,0,,awaiting our High Collar Lady?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.98,0:01:48.53,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fade(100,0)\c&HDDEEEF&\bord0\blur1.001\pos(741.85,149.54)}Episode 31 \N{\fs79.999}No Tears Left to Cry {ああ涙もかれ果てて}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.15,0:02:05.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Commander!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.50,0:02:08.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Sergeant Onijima!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.06,0:02:09.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! You found anyone?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.72,0:02:10.74,Default,,0,0,0,,No luck!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.97,0:02:14.87,Default,,0,0,0,,How'd it go?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.87,0:02:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It's no use!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.76,0:02:17.17,Default,,0,0,0,,They're nowhere to be found.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.17,0:02:18.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's give up.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.52,0:02:22.42,Default,,0,0,0,,This could only mean that both Commander and Sergeant Onijima have died in battle{/they've both died in battle}.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.17,0:02:26.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Our enemies are not just the partisans and the Cossack cavalry.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.22,0:02:30.63,Default,,0,0,0,,We mustn't take wolves and this blizzard lightly either.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.85,0:02:34.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Even Napoleon himself was defeated by Russian snow.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.51,0:02:36.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, let's march back!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.30,0:02:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Never!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.89,0:02:40.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll try once again, even on my own!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.50,0:02:43.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Kobayashi, I understand how you feel,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.48,0:02:46.78,Default,,0,0,0,,but we've exhausted our options.\NLet's go home now!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.67,0:02:51.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not going anywhere without our commander!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.74,0:02:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Second Lieutenant Ijuuin is the only one who has ever treated outcasts like us humanely!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.64,0:03:03.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd rather die alongside someone like him!\NYou go home without me!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.31,0:03:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll go look for him alone!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.59,0:03:07.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Kobayashi!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.84,0:03:09.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Commander!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.76,0:03:11.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Kobayashi!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.05,0:03:16.26,Default,,0,0,0,,We're not gonna leave you one!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.66,0:03:18.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, let's give it another shot!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.98,0:03:20.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Commander!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.57,0:03:22.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Kobayashi!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.02,0:03:22.35,Overlap,,0,0,0,,Commander!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.35,0:03:24.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Commander!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.76,0:03:25.04,Overlap,,0,0,0,,Commander!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.79,0:03:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Commander!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.86,0:03:32.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Commander!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.29,0:03:33.45,Overlap,,0,0,0,,Commander!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.34,0:03:48.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It's autumn already.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.17,0:03:50.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, just look at all of these ginkgo nuts.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.16,0:03:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Found one already!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.10,0:03:59.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I could ask Kisaragi to make some \Nomelet with it today! {chawanmushi; savoury steamed egg custard with chicken, mushrooms, etc.}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.77,0:04:01.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, or roast them and eat them here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.95,0:04:05.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, nice idea.\NLet's put them on the bonfire.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.82,0:04:07.89,Default,,0,0,0,,This brings back memories, actually.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.89,0:04:12.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you remember when we used to go to the botanical garden to gather ginkgo nuts?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.53,0:04:16.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course I do. We'd go there all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.75,0:04:21.64,Default,,0,0,0,,One for Ranmaru, one for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.64,0:04:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Two for Benio, two for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.84,0:04:29.65,Default,,0,0,0,,We'd keep going until we'd get so full we'd have a stomachache!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.01,0:04:33.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The stench of the ginkgo nuts would stick to our kimonos, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.16,0:04:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Nanny used to scold me for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.47,0:04:40.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Why can't we just go back the way we were?{Why couldn't we have stayed that way?}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.81,0:04:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Ranmaru...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.56,0:04:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry. I'm doing nothing but troubling you by talking about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.61,0:04:51.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Not at all. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.57,0:04:54.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder when Shinobu's coming back.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.78,0:05:01.10,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, 13,000 people are making their return on October 18th,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.10,0:05:04.04,Default,,0,0,0,,while some of them have already come back.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.97,0:05:14.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Army performance in Russia was far from stellar
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.59,0:05:16.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and, with recession around the corner,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.53,0:05:21.93,Default,,0,0,0,,the expeditionary forces were repatriated en masse from October to December 1918.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.78,0:05:35.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Good question. I'm sure he will also be back in no time, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.37,0:05:41.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}That day, I'll bring many bottles of vodka for us to drink.{\i0}{ref: ep 27, 11:18.21}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.95,0:05:46.58,Default,,0,0,0,,He made me a promise. He swore that he'd be back.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.79,0:05:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Lady Benio! Lady Benio!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.71,0:05:59.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? Good timing, Kisaragi.\NWe've just finished roasting ginkgo nuts.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.47,0:06:01.22,Default,,0,0,0,,This is not the time for that!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.22,0:06:03.72,Default,,0,0,0,,C-Countess has just collapsed.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.72,0:06:04.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.68,0:06:05.64,Default,,0,0,0,,How come?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.37,0:06:08.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Countess?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.57,0:06:13.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's all just hurry home. Quick!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.33,0:06:26.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Stay strong, Countess.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.20,0:06:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.00,0:06:30.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Shinobu... Shinobu...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.17,0:06:32.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Countess?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.59,0:06:37.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Watch out, you're too close.\NYou'll end up falling into the pond...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.46,0:06:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Countess...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.80,0:06:40.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Shinobu...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.01,0:06:41.80,Default,,0,0,0,,My Shinobu...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.72,0:06:46.66,Default,,0,0,0,,This way, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.64,0:06:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,She's been muttering for a while, I hope she'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.94,0:06:53.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll inject her a sedative.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.34,0:06:57.24,Default,,0,0,0,,At times like these, resting properly is the best one can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.96,0:06:59.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Lady Benio.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.24,0:06:59.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.82,0:07:03.17,Default,,0,0,0,,There are some visitors that wish to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.58,0:07:07.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to leave Countess's side right now...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.08,0:07:10.30,Default,,0,0,0,,But you see, they said that it's urgent.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.30,0:07:12.50,Default,,0,0,0,,There's also your father among them.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.50,0:07:14.52,Default,,0,0,0,,What? My father?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.63,0:07:17.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Who could they be?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.01,0:07:21.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Long time no see, father.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.34,0:07:24.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Benio, these men are{/were} Shinobu's subordinates.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.14,0:07:27.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, so you are Lady Benio.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.88,0:07:30.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you the fiancée Second Lieutenant told us about?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.74,0:07:31.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.54,0:07:34.86,Default,,0,0,0,,W-We're extremely honored to meet you!{/It's an honor to meet you}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.86,0:07:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The pleasure is all mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.28,0:07:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Second Lieutenant used to talk about you all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.03,0:07:46.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}My Benio is ever so kind and cheerful...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.29,0:07:51.17,Default,,0,0,0,,He'd never get tired of talking like that about you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.23,0:07:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Cheerful...?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.80,0:07:56.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Shinobu...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.74,0:07:57.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.13,0:08:05.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Our unit was sent to the most dangerous front line before the other ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.05,0:08:09.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Being a gathering of rogues, we've always been treated poorly by our superiors
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.73,0:08:14.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and on the final day of our assignment, our headquarters left us to our death.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.69,0:08:16.86,Default,,0,0,0,,We got surrounded by a Cossack formation.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.19,0:08:21.91,Default,,0,0,0,,We desperately tried to make our way out and ran for dear life.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.86,0:08:18.78,Top,,0,0,0,,Platoon, attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.72,0:08:28.91,Default,,0,0,0,,However, Sergeant Onijima, \Nour deputy commander, got injured,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.91,0:08:32.79,Default,,0,0,0,,yet we couldn't afford \Nto wait for him to catch up with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.19,0:08:37.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Shinobu has told me a lot about him in his letters.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.21,0:08:42.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Commander couldn't leave him behind.\NSo he said to us...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.51,0:08:46.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We'll return to Japan all together. \NGet moving!{\i0}{ref: ep 30, 19:48.83}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.26,0:08:47.18,Default,,0,0,0,,We couldn't stop him
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.64,0:08:50.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and, with those words,\Nhe ran among bombings all alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.61,0:08:54.77,Default,,0,0,0,,He was the only one of us \Nwho returned to look for Sergeant Onijima.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.77,0:08:58.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Despite our selfish superiors having abandoned us to our fate,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.33,0:09:04.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Second Lieutenant just refused to leave even a single one of us behind...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.13,0:09:12.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I... I'd never met a commander like him!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.44,0:09:15.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if we are just lowlifes,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.42,0:09:19.38,Default,,0,0,0,,he declared he wouldn't let anyone die in vain.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.00,0:09:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,He's the only one to who's ever treated us like human beings.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.18,0:09:31.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Throughout our lives, people have always regarded us as nothing more than pests.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.77,0:09:36.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Only Second Lieutenant was different,\Nprotecting us like he was our big brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.03,0:09:37.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And now he's...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.50,0:10:01.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Shinobu...!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.22,0:10:05.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Shinobu!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.58,0:10:08.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Shinobu! Shinobu!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.01,0:10:12.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa, Benio!\NHang in there, Benio!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.14,0:10:18.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Father, I don't understand \Nwhat you all are trying to say...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.22,0:10:21.93,Default,,0,0,0,,What in the world are you trying to tell me?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.36,0:10:28.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Benio, I don't want to believe it either, \Nbut Second Lieutenant Ijuuin... died in battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.07,0:10:34.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Shinobu... is... dead...?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.91,0:10:38.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(0,800)\shad20\4c&H7C7C88&\4a&H7C&\i1}I'll return home for sure...{\i0}{it's the vodka line, but it wouldn't work in this situation}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.54,0:10:41.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(0,800)\shad20\4c&H7C7C88&\4a&H7C&\i1}I'll return home for sure...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.27,0:10:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(0,5800)\shad20\4c&H7C7C88&\4a&H7C&\i1}I'll return home for sure...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.93,0:11:00.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Shinobu! I thought you promised you'd be back!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.86,0:11:02.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Shinobu...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.83,0:11:21.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Countess, here, please sit on this chair.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.34,0:11:28.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I am Count Ijuuin, the owner of this mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.39,0:11:29.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\3c&H491900&}Sir!\N{\3c}Sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.07,0:11:31.32,Default,,0,0,0,,We've heard many great things about you!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.32,0:11:33.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Good. Well, at ease, boys.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.35,0:11:35.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been a long time, Count.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.81,0:11:38.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm here today to express my condolences for Shinobu's passing.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.10,0:11:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Please tell us everything about Shinobu, even minor details.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.19,0:11:47.61,Default,,0,0,0,,We'd like to, but every memory wrings our hearts even more.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.99,0:11:56.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! Don't forget that you're still imperial soldiers!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.91,0:12:00.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Leave the tears to women and children!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.04,0:12:01.83,Default,,0,0,0,,As men, you must never...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.21,0:12:08.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Never lose your composure! Never!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.97,0:12:18.37,Default,,0,0,0,,At first,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.10,0:12:21.24,Default,,0,0,0,,we all had hastily assumed Second Lieutenant
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.77,0:12:24.56,Default,,0,0,0,,was just another spoiled heir of a rich family
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.56,0:12:26.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and belittled him.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.82,0:12:30.91,Default,,0,0,0,,However, we soon realized he actually was more human than anyone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.86,0:12:35.53,Default,,0,0,0,,That's obvious! It's our family's trademark, after all. So what's next?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.53,0:12:39.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a tattoo on this arm,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.12,0:12:44.35,Default,,0,0,0,,which has always been enough for me to be respected,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.35,0:12:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,but that wasn't of any help when it came to letters from home.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.92,0:12:54.76,Default,,0,0,0,,While everyone else received them from their loved ones in Japan,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.76,0:12:56.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I, being an orphan,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.05,0:12:58.51,Default,,0,0,0,,was always the exception.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.56,0:13:04.83,Default,,0,0,0,,That was when Second Lieutenant introduced me some White Russian orphans
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.83,0:13:07.56,Default,,0,0,0,,who lost their parents during the revolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.56,0:13:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,He offered me to become their Japanese teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.88,0:13:15.80,Top,,0,0,0,,A, i, u, e, o!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.82,0:13:17.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth be told, I didn't even finish elementary school myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.70,0:13:21.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though many in our unit had high school and even university diplomas,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.71,0:13:26.14,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\c&H294D73&\3c&H06133D&\blur1.001\fax-0.057558\fscx101.092\fscy123.74\frx10.3429\fry-2.8456\xbord4.24\ybord4.95\org(1310,321)\pos(1316.179,197.79)\frz349.9\bord1.001}IVAN
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.72,0:13:26.14,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\c&H294D73&\3c&H06133D&\blur1.001\fax-0.208256\fscx94.369\fscy100.98\frx17.4436\fry0.0369\xbord3.96\ybord4.04\org(1182,56)\pos(1187.769,30.63)\frz355.8\bord1.001}NIKOLAI
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.72,0:13:26.14,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\c&H294D73&\3c&H06133D&\blur1.001\fax-0.283936\fscx95.526\fscy103.98\frx10.7890\fry-11.1648\ybord4.16\org(888,38)\pos(895.48,12.941)\frz357.1\bord1.001}NATASHA
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.72,0:13:26.14,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\c&H294D73&\3c&H06133D&\blur1.001\fax-0.217635\fscx93.376\fscy116.19\frx17.3697\fry-4.2025\xbord3.92\ybord4.65\org(574,62)\pos(580.08,32.2)\frz353.5\bord1.001}KOBAYASHI
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.35,0:13:27.42,Default,,0,0,0,,he still chose someone like me, completely unbecoming of a professor.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.02,0:13:31.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So, in the beginning, I was at a loss.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.72,0:13:41.81,Default,,0,0,0,,But, thanks to this, when we were leaving for the front line,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.81,0:13:46.12,Default,,0,0,0,,the kids came to see us off, waving small Japanese flags.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.69,0:13:58.62,Default,,0,0,0,,In that moment, I vowed to sacrifice my own life for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.58,0:14:06.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks to Second Lieutenant, I found my new little sisters and brothers in Siberia.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.04,0:14:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It was him who granted an orphan like me with a reason to live for.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.34,0:14:19.43,Default,,0,0,0,,We may never meet again...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.03,0:14:24.47,Default,,0,0,0,,but, whenever I close my eyes, I see those Siberian children...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.04,0:14:28.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and I feel like I'm there with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.85,0:14:32.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Only someone like him could make this happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.21,0:14:36.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Shinobu was very much like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.50,0:14:40.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Dear, a Satsuma warrior \Nshouldn't be crying before the survivors...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.34,0:14:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not crying!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.14,0:14:45.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Who're you taking me for?! \NI'm just sweating from my eyes!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.85,0:15:12.67,Default,,0,0,0,,From that day onward, Countess has been sleeping for days on end due to the shock.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.86,0:15:18.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Meanwhile, Count has shut himself in his room.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.42,0:15:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,When he comes out every now and then,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.84,0:15:24.83,Default,,0,0,0,,his eyes are clearly red and swollen.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.23,0:15:27.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Why? Why did it have to be Young Master?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.10,0:15:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Our immeasurably kind Young Master...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.25,0:15:37.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The whole household spends its days crying.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.60,0:15:42.74,Default,,0,0,0,,No one can bear the thought of you being gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.47,0:15:47.78,Default,,0,0,0,,No one can bear the thought of living \Nwhile you’re gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.16,0:15:50.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Shinobu...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.35,0:15:56.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Benio, Shinobu's funeral is tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.79,0:16:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.28,0:16:07.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Why...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.41,0:16:12.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Why won't any tears come out?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.67,0:16:14.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't cry.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.30,0:16:19.90,Default,,0,0,0,,My throat is obstructed by grief\Nand I can't speak.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.63,0:16:23.75,Default,,0,0,0,,My eyes are clogged\Nand I can't shed any tears.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.39,0:16:32.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't stand this pain in my chest...!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.77,0:16:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... The very thought of your love...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.02,0:16:40.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like being desperately trying \Nto get out of a whirlpool.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.49,0:16:47.47,Default,,0,0,0,,All of these emotions are about to tear my chest apart...!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.04,0:16:52.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'll come home for sure. I promise. Safe and sound.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.59,0:17:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't you tell me so?! \NYou {\i1}have{\i0} to come back!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.76,0:17:08.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You {\i1}must{\i0} come back, and then at least \NI could tell you about my feelings! 
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.41,0:17:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a lie. It has to be. \NIt can't be true that you're gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.32,0:17:28.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, what's with that woman?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.09,0:17:31.22,Default,,0,0,0,,What a weird girl. Why is she out in this rain without an umbrella?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.47,0:17:38.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't believe it. \NI don't want to believe it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.13,0:17:44.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Why? Why didn't you come back?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.93,0:17:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Why... Didn't you appear before me \Nlike you always did?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.56,0:18:02.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Boy, let me tell you about your father{ぼうやお聞きよ、お父様 - lyrics from the manga - I don't know if it's sung from the father's POV}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.53,0:18:07.80,Default,,0,0,0,,who went to Siberia, where flowers bloom...{花咲くところのシベリアに}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.26,0:18:14.20,Default,,0,0,0,,We might never meet again{おいでののちはひとたびも}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.20,0:18:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,for this could be my final moment.{idk}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.08,0:18:25.48,Default,,0,0,0,,At the battle of Nikolayevsk... {there wasn't really a battle, just a massacre - perevodildo}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.02,0:18:24.97,Overlap,,0,0,0,,At the battle of Nikolayevsk...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.09,0:18:28.74,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why they were left behind...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.30,0:18:32.35,Default,,0,0,0,,That's when that a partisan stabbed you
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.79,0:18:35.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and you drew your last breath...!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.81,0:18:37.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Shinobu!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.15,0:18:39.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Shinobu!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.15,0:18:42.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Shinobu!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.46,0:18:45.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Shinobu! Shinobu!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.74,0:18:54.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa, whoa, whoa!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.83,0:18:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You sure have a lot of energies, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.88,0:19:02.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Gonna leave without even \Napologizing, eh, young miss?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.13,0:19:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Army uniforms...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.89,0:19:07.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Precisely. As you can see, we are imperial soldiers!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.54,0:19:11.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa there. Hold on. \NWho said you can just leave without saying anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.34,0:19:16.47,Default,,0,0,0,,How about you hang out with us for a while as a token of apology?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.47,0:19:17.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, what do you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.77,0:19:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Come now!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.52,0:19:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you've done it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.48,0:19:26.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that a way to treat an imperial soldier?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.66,0:19:28.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You're too impertinent for a woman!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.20,0:19:30.28,Default,,0,0,0,,What am {\i1}I{\i0} doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.28,0:19:33.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Then tell me, what have {\i1}you{\i0} done for Shinobu?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.66,0:19:37.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You sent him to his certain death while you were twiddling your thumbs!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.79,0:19:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I won't forgive you!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.96,0:19:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyone or anything that played a role in taking Shinobu away from me won't get away with it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.25,0:19:45.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You broad...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.18,0:19:57.20,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a fight!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.20,0:19:59.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I-It's a fight! They're fighting!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.39,0:20:00.60,Default,,0,0,0,,S-She fought them!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.60,0:20:01.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.90,0:20:05.61,Default,,0,0,0,,A woman is thrashing four soldiers by herself!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.36,0:20:10.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Someone stop them! I beg you!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.45,0:20:12.46,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll need an ambulance if this keeps up!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.46,0:20:16.03,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no way that she can win in a one-to-five.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.03,0:20:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You got this wrong! It's the soldiers who'll need it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.80,0:20:19.58,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.21,0:20:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,We got beaten up...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.60,0:20:30.26,Default,,0,0,0,,See? It's what comes after that's scary. Hospital bills don't come cheap these days.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.59,0:20:33.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Boss! Let's hurry up to get out of here, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.55,0:20:35.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, you!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.47,0:20:37.81,Default,,0,0,0,,They're already here, Boss!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.81,0:20:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on now! Hurry up!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.60,0:20:40.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Who did this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.20,0:20:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Who made such a mess of these soldiers?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.44,0:20:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it was me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.00,0:20:48.86,Default,,0,0,0,,No way you did it with that face of yours!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.86,0:20:50.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh... that hurt...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.82,0:20:54.62,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\c&H2A2D28&\3c&H2C5850&\fax-0.301397\fscx67.203\fscy104.03\frz14.2981\frx9.5718\fry-10.4889\xbord2.82\ybord4.16\org(1145,213)\pos(1150.66,187.481)}Ueno Police Station {上野警察署}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.50,0:21:04.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you ever gonna open your mouth?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.74,0:21:06.85,Default,,0,0,0,,What's your name? Where do you live?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.29,0:21:09.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Who's gonna answer in your place?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.88,0:21:15.80,Default,,0,0,0,,How in the world did a woman like you manage to beat up five imperial soldiers?! {he says four, but there were five before unless I'm tripping} 
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.72,0:21:22.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Ugh, at least show some remorse!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.08,0:21:27.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll stay here until someone more mature comes for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.74,0:21:43.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Sheesh, we're in a pickle...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.54,0:21:45.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if she brings Count up,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.48,0:21:50.09,Default,,0,0,0,,she'll just give him and Countess, \Nwho are already grieving, more to worry about.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.80,0:21:55.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Boss may be foul-mouthed, but there's no way she'll mention Count.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.16,0:22:00.01,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, this means no one's coming for her, so she'll never get out.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.93,0:22:03.43,Default,,0,0,0,,But tomorrow's the day of Second Lieutenant's funeral...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.99,0:22:18.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Wherever Benio looks, \Nbe it to the West or to the East,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.37,0:22:21.33,Default,,0,0,0,,there will always be a cold wall before her.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.83,0:22:24.56,Default,,0,0,0,,All that comes to her feverish mind
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.56,0:22:28.42,Default,,0,0,0,,is Shinobu's gallant image.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.17,0:22:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,But this doesn't change the fact that tomorrow his funeral will be held.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.76,0:22:45.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is she refusing to utter the Count's name in order to leave this police cell?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.37,0:22:54.32,Sign,,0,0,0,,Next episode of Here Comes High Collar Lady
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.32,0:22:58.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Various relatives of the Ijuuin family, who gathered for Shinobu's funeral,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.75,0:23:02.70,Default,,0,0,0,,start shameful fights when discussing how to share their fortune.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.70,0:23:06.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Benio declares her eternal and unchanging love for Shinobu,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.58,0:23:11.29,Default,,0,0,0,,donning her white dress and cutting off her black hair afterwards.{what - perevodildo}{huh? I'll see if it makes sense the next episode lol - alucard}{seems this "black hair" thing is a part of a set phrase, regardless of the actual color}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.29,0:23:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, how is she going to live from now on?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.00,0:23:19.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Next time on Here Comes High Collar Lady: \NI'll Cut my Black Hair to Consecrate it to You.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.61,0:23:21.44,Sign,,0,0,0,,Episode 32 \NI'll Cut my Black Hair to Consecrate it to You {黒髪きって捧げます}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.20,0:23:20.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't miss it!
